About this time, probably, Domitian (as Claudius did before him) banishes the Jews from the city, and the grove of the Muses (which had been con- secrated by Numa) is let to them (Sat. 3. 13 ; 6. 542).

Consuls, Marcus Cornelius Fronto, the 3d time, with Trajan (3d time).

Martial the poet dies in his native town of Bilbilis, in Celtiberia, to which he repaired from Rome, An. Ch. 100, (or according to Dodwell, 103), and died shortly after. His epigrams show that he was on the most intimate terms with Juvenal. It is conjectured from the strain of some epigrams which Martial composed after his return to Bil- bilis, that Juvenal was then in Rome, not in Egypt·
